children.subject: what other technicals and recruiting / research? Depends on how much classwork those are

history.content: I did that over the summer and it was pretty manageable/not much time commitment. It might actually be easier during the semester because over the summer 70 ai's had to teach/lead breakout rooms so they had to spend some time prepping beforehand. 61B AI is also relatively chill, really depends on how fast you can complete the labs beforehand. You might be a little ambitious with doing that with 3 techs (especially 61c)/research and recruiting though.

I was wondering if it would be practical to AI for 2 classes concurrently (CS61B and CS70). I enjoyed both classes and am interested in staying involved with them. For context I’m taking CS61C and 2 other technicals this semester and also intend to do recruiting/research. Would it be better to just choose one class or is 2 manageable?
history.subject: Interning for 2 classes
